Preheat your oven to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Cut the @potatoes{450%g} lengthways into 1cm slices, then cut into 1cm wide fries
(no need to peel).

Pop the fries onto a large #baking tray{}. Drizzle with @oil{}, sprinkle over half
the @Central American style spice mix{1} (half for fries), season with @salt{}
and @pepper{}, then toss to coat. Spread out in a single layer.

> Use two baking trays if necessary.

When the oven is hot, bake on the top shelf until golden, ~{25-30%minutes}.

Meanwhile, drain the @halloumi{225%g}, then cut it into 3 slices per person.
Place into a #medium bowl{} of cold water and leave to soak.

Halve, peel and thinly slice the @red onion{1/2}(peeled and thinly sliced).
In a #small bowl{}, combine the red onion, @sugar for the pickle{1} (for pickling),
half the @cider vinegar{30%ml} and a pinch of @salt{}. Set aside.

Drain the @sweetcorn{150%g} in a #sieve{}. Halve the @baby plum tomatoes{125%g}.
Pop the corn and tomatoes into another medium bowl with a drizzle of @oil{}
. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then set aside.

== Buffalo Style Sauce ==

Pop a #large frying pan{} on medium-high heat. Pour in the @water for the sauce{50%ml}
and remaining cider vinegar. Bring to the boil, lower to medium heat and simmer
until reduced by half, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Stir in the @sriracha sauce{15%ml} and @honey{15%ml}. Simmer until thickened,
~{1-2%minutes}, then remove from the heat.

> If your honey has hardened, pop it in a #bowl{} of hot water for 1 minute.

Stir in the @butter{20%g} until melted, then remove from the heat. Transfer your
buffalo sauce to a small bowl.

== Crispy Halloumi ==

Remove the halloumi slices from the cold water and pat dry with #kitchen paper{}.
Sprinkle over the remaining Central American style spice mix.

Wipe out the (now empty) halloumi bowl, then crack the @egg{1} into it and whisk.

Put the @panko breadcrumbs{50%g} into another bowl and season with @salt{} and
@pepper{}.

Dip the halloumi into the egg, then the breadcrumbs, ensuring it's completely
coated. Shake off the excess and transfer to a #plate{}.

== Spiced Fries and Burger Assembly ==

Clean out the (now empty) #frying pan{} and put back on high heat with enough
@oil{} to completely coat the bottom of the pan.

> You want the oil to be hot so the halloumi fries properly - heat for 2-3 mins
before you add the halloumi.

Once the oil is hot, carefully lay in the halloumi, reduce the heat to medium-high
and fry until golden-brown, ~{7-8%minutes} total. Turn every couple of minutes
and reduce the heat if needed.

Meanwhile, halve the @burger buns{2} and pop them into the oven to warm through,
~{2-3%minutes}.

== Assembly ==

To build your burgers, spread the @mayonnaise{2%tbsp} over the bun bases. Stack
the halloumi on top, then drizzle over the buffalo sauce. Top with some of the
@wild rocket{40%g} and pickled onion, then close with the bun lid.

Add any remaining rocket and pickled onion (including the pickling liquid) to
the tomato and corn bowl, then toss together.

Serve your craft burgers with the spicy fries and salad on the side. Enjoy!